Package com.mycompany.hw4_2

Class KWPriorityMaxQueue<E>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
com.mycompany.hw4_2.KWPriorityMaxQueue<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The data type of objects in the priority queue
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Queue<E>
public class KWPriorityMaxQueue<E>
extends AbstractQueue<E>
implements Queue<E>
The KWPriorityQueue implements the Queue interface by building a heap in an ArrayList. The heap is structured so that the "smallest" item is at the top.
Author:
Jacob / Koffman & Wolfgang
